<h2><span id="What_is_Ikaho_Onsen_Ishidan-gai"><b>What is Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai?</b></span></h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3867" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image14-1-e1646196799516.jpg" alt="ikahoishidangai" width="591" height="422"></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai is a stone staircase that was built about 400 years ago when the Ikaho Hot Spring was first opened. A total of 365 stone steps were built with the hope that the hot spring resort would be bustling all year round. Both sides of the stone steps are lined with spots for eating and drinking, amusement areas for shooting and ring-tossing, footbaths, and hot spring inns, making this a place where you can make many happy memories.</span></p>
<h2><span id="Ikaho_Onsen_Ishidan-gai_Stone_Steps_Street_Day_Trip_Report"><b>Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai (Stone Steps Street) Day Trip Report</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This time, I actually visited Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai and took a day trip there. I will introduce some of the gourmet food, fun, and souvenirs I found there, so please take a look. Also, at the beginning and end of this article, you will find information on the Gunma-Yokohama New Star Bus (highway bus) that we used on our way to and from Yokohama. Please refer to it as well.</span></p>
<h3><span id="900_Departed_from_Roppongi_Hills"><strong>9:00 Departed from Roppongi Hills</strong></span></h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3863" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image13.jpg" alt="roppongi" width="591" height="443" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image13.jpg 591w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image13-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">8:30 arrived at Roppongi Station! After using the restroom at Roppongi Hills, we headed for the bus stop.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3875" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image16-1.jpg" alt="roppongi" width="443" height="422" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image16-1.jpg 443w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image16-1-300x286.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The road to the bus stop is a bit confusing, so please be careful. Just follow the arrow on the pillar that says &#8220;Group Bus Stop&#8221; and you will get there.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3871" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image15-1.jpg" alt="roppongi" width="443" height="506" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image15-1.jpg 443w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image15-1-263x300.jpg 263w" sizes="(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When we arrived at the boarding area, there were already about eight people lined up. There was a cold snap that day, but I didn&#8217;t feel too cold because I was underground.</span></p>
<p><strong>Details of the boarding station;</strong></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">・Vending machines are available<br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">・No convenience store<br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">・No toilets<br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">・No smoking area<br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">・No coin lockers</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are no convenience stores nearby, so it is recommended that you buy everything you need in advance.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3883" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image18-1.jpg" alt="roppongi" width="443" height="591" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image18-1.jpg 443w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image18-1-225x300.jpg 225w" sizes="(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At around 8:50, the Gunma-Yokohama New Star arrived! Our journey to Gunma had finally begun.</span></p>

		<style type="text/css">
