		</style>
		<div id='gallery-1' class='gallery galleryid-3794 gallery-columns-2 gallery-size-full'><dl class='gallery-item'>
			<dt class='gallery-icon landscape'>
				<a href='https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/destination/3794/attachment/image17-3/'><img width="300" height="225" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image17-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full" alt="bus" loading="lazy" /></a>
			</dt></dl><dl class='gallery-item'>
			<dt class='gallery-icon landscape'>
				<a href='https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/destination/3794/attachment/image21-4/'><img width="300" height="225" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image21.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full" alt="" loading="lazy" /></a>
			</dt></dl><br style="clear: both" />
		</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Details of the bus<br />
</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">・Trunk room available (one per person, up to 1m in total length and width, up to 10kg)<br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">・Disinfectant and antibacterial treatment were available.<br />
</span>・Babies are welcome (child fare is required to use a seat, foldable strollers are allowed, but not electric ones).<br />
・USB charging is available.<br />
・No restroom</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There will be a 15-minute break at the Miyoshi Service Area and Kamisato Service Area.</span></p>
<h3><span id="1230_arrived_at_Ikaho_Onsen_Ishidan-gai_Exit"><strong>12:30 arrived at Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai Exit.</strong></span></h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3891" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image20.jpg" alt="ikahoishidangai" width="591" height="443" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image20.jpg 591w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image20-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After a three-and-a-half-hour bus ride, we arrived at the Ikaho Onsen stone terrace entrance. Perhaps it was because we had taken two breaks at the service areas, but we were hardly tired. We went to the stone staircase in high spirits!</span></p>
<h3><span id="First_we_prayed_for_a_good_marriage_at_Ikaho_Shrine"><span style="font-weight: 400;">First, we prayed for a good marriage at Ikaho Shrine.</span></span></h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3795" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image24-e1646197178639.jpg" alt="Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai" width="443" height="443"></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To spend half the day there comfortably, we decided to start off with Ikaho Shrine first. The Ikaho Shrine is located at the top of 365 stone steps. You might be thinking, &#8220;365 steps? You might think, &#8220;365 steps out of nowhere?&#8221; but it is recommended to climb them first so you can get a general idea of where everything is.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3899" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image22-e1646197207886.jpg" alt="Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai" width="591" height="395"></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After climbing up the stone steps for about ten minutes, we arrived at the top. This is not a big shrine, but it has a gentle and warm atmosphere, as if it is watching over the people from the top of the mountain.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3903" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image23.jpg" alt="Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai" width="443" height="534" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image23.jpg 443w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image23-249x300.jpg 249w" sizes="(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After my visit, I also received a red seal at the shrine office. When you look at Gunma Prefecture from above, it&#8217;s shaped like a crane, so there&#8217;s a crane on the top left and a sincere turtle on the other side. It&#8217;s a powerful good luck charm that has a red seal with a crane and a turtle.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3799" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image25.jpg" alt="Ikaho Onsen Ishidan-gai" width="591" height="443" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image25.jpg 591w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image25-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After carefully tucking them into your bag, you will head down the stone stairs to lunch.</span></p>
<p><b>Basic information about Ikaho Shrine</b></p>
