<h3><span id="Looking_for_souvenirs_is_one_of_the_best_parts_of_traveling"><b>Looking for souvenirs is one of the best parts of traveling.</b></span></h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3827" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image4-2.jpg" alt="ikaho-onsen-ishidangai" width="591" height="443" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image4-2.jpg 591w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image4-2-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It was almost time for us to leave. At the end of the day, it was time to hit the souvenir shops and find your favorite one. The following three stores are highly recommended in Ishidan-gai.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3831" src="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image5-2.jpg" alt="ikaho-onsen-ishidangai" width="591" height="443" srcset="https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image5-2.jpg 591w, https://japanbusonline.com/bus-repo/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/image5-2-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you want to buy handicrafts I recommend Yamashiraya. The shop sells many original goods that are fun to look at, such as ornaments featuring Gunma&#8217;s famous Daruma Doll, and rabbit and cat goods. All of the goods are really cute and I spent way too much time deciding which to buy.</span></p>
<p><b>Yamashiroya Details</b></p>
<table style="width: 99.2129%;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 30.5633%; text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Business Hours</span></td>
<td style="width: 118.427%; text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">10:00 &#8211; 18:00 sometimes closed irregularly</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="width: 30.5633%; text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Address</span></td>
<td style="width: 118.427%; text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">12 Ikaho, Ikaho-cho, Shibukawa City (271st stone staircase)</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="width: 30.5633%; text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Phone Number</span></td>
<td style="width: 118.427%; text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">0279-72-2239</span></td>
</tr>
